    <item>
      <title>Which universities should one apply to?</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 00:51:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/which-universities-should-one-apply-to.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/which-universities-should-one-apply-to/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;which-universities-should-one-apply-to&#34;&gt;Which universities should one apply to?&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A college degree is not a sign that one is a finished product but an indication a person is prepared for life.&#xA;— Edward Malloy&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Going to college is a major event in one&amp;rsquo;s education, but the choice of exactly which college to go to is not as critical as it is sometimes portrayed to be; usually, there will be several good choices that suit your specific strengths and weaknesses, and it is not absolutely necessary to secure the &amp;ldquo;best&amp;rdquo; choice for your undergraduate or graduate education. I would recommend a flexible attitude towards this decision; by focusing too much on one institution, you might overlook others which may in fact be a better fit for you.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Don’t prematurely obsess on a single “big problem” or “big theory”</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 19:04:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;dont-prematurely-obsess-on-a-single-big-problem-or-big-theory&#34;&gt;Don’t prematurely obsess on a single &amp;ldquo;big problem&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;big theory&amp;rdquo;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Millions long for immortality who do not know what to do with themselves on a rainy Sunday afternoon.&#xA;— Susan Ertz, &amp;ldquo;Anger in the Sky&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There is a particularly dangerous occupational hazard in this subject: one can become focused, to the exclusion of other mathematical activity (and in extreme cases, on non-mathematical activity also), on a single really difficult problem in a field (or on some grand unifying theory) before one is really ready (both in terms of mathematical preparation, and also in terms of one&amp;rsquo;s career) to devote so much of one&amp;rsquo;s research time to such a project. This is doubly true if one has not yet &lt;strong&gt;learnt the limitations of one&amp;rsquo;s tools&lt;/strong&gt; or acquired a healthy &lt;strong&gt;scepticism of one&amp;rsquo;s own work&lt;/strong&gt;, as this can lead to the humiliating spectacle of proudly announcing a major breakthrough on a well known problem, only to withdraw the preprint shortly afterwards after serious flaws (often arising from pushing a method well beyond its known limits, and encounting obstructions beyond those limits that were known to the experts) are pointed out in the manuscript.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
